    "refcode_long": "Counsels on Sabbath School Work, p. 104.1 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "We must have consecrated teachers, who love God supremely and their neighbors as themselves. The Lord has made ample provision that teachers may have increased ability from Sabbath to Sabbath, that they may teach to some purpose, working as for time and eternity. We need in our schools young men and women who have vital godliness, not a cheap, superficial experience, but a deep inward piety that results from learning daily in the school of Christ, that they may impart to others the precious lessons which Christ has taught them.",
    "puborder": 297,
    "translations": [
